# Architecture rule

The authoritative design lives in `references/design/`:

- `00-overview.md` — system diagram, component inventory, runtime sequence, NFRs.
- `01-agents.md` — the 6 agents (Brand Analyst, Art Director, Generator, Critic, Model Orchestrator, Assembler) and their I/O.
- `02-data-contracts.md` — JSON schemas for every inter-agent handoff.
- `03-model-optimization.md` — the 7-point optimization story (O1–O7).
- `04-comfyui-workflow.md` — the FLUX+PuLID workflow + runner protocol.
- `05-frontend.md` — the Brand Kit Gallery + API contract.
- `06-deployment.md` — DGX Spark deployment + model optimization.

## Hard constraints

- The Art Director is the **delegating** agent; Analyst/Generator/Critic/Orchestrator are its tools. Do not flatten this into a linear script.
- Every inter-agent handoff is a **validated JSON file** (`brand_dna.json`, `asset_manifest.json`, `critic_result.json`, `kit_manifest.json`, `orchestrator_log.json`). Implement these as Pydantic models in `src/common/schemas.py` exactly matching `02-data-contracts.md`.
- Reasoning + generation are **local** (Nemotron via Ollama, ComfyUI FLUX). Vision understanding + critique use **Stepfun `step-3.7-flash`**. Cloud NVIDIA NIM is routing/failover only.
- The Model Orchestrator owns the Ollama↔ComfyUI VRAM swap; no other component may call `ollama stop`/`ollama load` directly.
- Every run is a self-contained dir under `runs/<run_id>/` with inputs, intermediates, renders, and `run.log`.

Any change that diverges from these docs must first update the affected design doc and note the divergence in the change packet.
